cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image matching and attribute transfer. The use of neural networks for learning and the focus on semantic attributes suggest that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of benchmarks and evaluation metrics suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
